    "This issue is compounded by the lack of shared accountability for AI malpractice.",
    "Currently, the burden of liability falls disproportionately on practitioners, with insufficient responsibility placed on vendors and institutions.",
    "This imbalance exacerbates the challenges of navigating the proprietary and opaque nature of many AI models used in healthcare, which often lack explainability and transparency, making it difficult to evaluate and address potential biases.",
    "Research by Gichoya et al.",
    "has shown that machine learning systems can predict racial identity from de-identified medical images, raising ethical concerns, particularly given the history of racial bias in U.S. healthcare."
